# Repository Patterns (PORTS & ADAPTERS)

**📚 Complete Guide**: `docs/conventions/patterns/repository-patterns.md`
**📖 Examples**: `docs/conventions/examples/user-management/complete-implementation.md`

## Critical Rules

- **Interface**: Domain layer — `packages/<context>/domain/repositories/[entity].repository.interface.ts`
- **Implementation**: Infrastructure layer — `packages/<context>/infrastructure/repositories/`
- **VO params**: ALL interface methods use VOs/entities — never `string`, `number`, `boolean`
- **Returns**: `Promise<Entity | null>` for single lookups — NOT `undefined`
- **`@Injectable()`**: Required on ALL concrete implementations
- **Hydration**: Use `Entity.reconstitute()` — NOT `Entity.fromDto()`

## Interface Template

```typescript
export interface IUserRepository {
  findAll(): Promise<User[]>
  findById(id: UserId): Promise<User | null>
  findByEmail(email: Email): Promise<User | null>
  save(user: User): Promise<void>
  delete(id: UserId): Promise<void>
}
```

## InMemory Implementation Template

```typescript
@Injectable()
export class InMemoryUserRepository implements IUserRepository {
  private readonly store = new Map<string, User>()

  async findById(id: UserId): Promise<User | null> {
    return this.store.get(id.getValue()) ?? null
  }

  async findByEmail(email: Email): Promise<User | null> {
    for (const u of this.store.values())
      if (u.email.getValue() === email.getValue()) return u
    return null
  }

  async save(user: User): Promise<void> {
    this.store.set(user.getId().getValue(), user)
  }

  async delete(id: UserId): Promise<void> {
    this.store.delete(id.getValue())
  }

  async findAll(): Promise<User[]> {
    return Array.from(this.store.values())
  }
}
```

## Entity Transformation

```typescript
// ✅ Reconstitute from persistence
User.reconstitute(record.id, record.email, record.passwordHash, record.role, record.createdAt, record.resetToken)

// ✅ Serialize to persistence
const dto = user.toDto()   // uses .getValue() internally

// ❌ Never use fromDto()
User.fromDto(record)
```

## DI Binding

```typescript
@Injectable()
export class SomeService {
  constructor(
    @Inject(InMemoryUserRepository)      // concrete token
    private readonly repo: IUserRepository,  // interface type
  ) {}
}
```
